17 under subsection (a) of this Code section such member shall receive a monthly service
18 retirement allowance equal to the sum of $50.00 for each year of such member's creditable
19 service and an additional $200.00 for each year of such member's presiding creditable
20 service. Any inactive or retired member who was not a contributing member on January 1,
21 2022, and who becomes a contributing member again after January 1, 2022, shall be
22 eligible for the monthly service retirement allowance provided in this subsection for his or
23 her membership service earned after January 1, 2022.
24 (c.2) In lieu of the monthly service retirement allowance provided in subsection (c.1) or (d)
25 of this Code section, for any person who was a contributing member on January 1, 2026,
26 or who first becomes a contributing member after January 1, 2026, upon retirement under
27 subsection (a) of this Code section such member shall receive a monthly service retirement
28 allowance equal to the sum of $75.00 for each year of such member's creditable service and
29 an additional $300.00 for each year of such member's presiding creditable service. Any
30 inactive or retired member who was not a contributing member on January 1, 2026, and
31 who becomes a contributing member again after January 1, 2026, shall be eligible for the
32 monthly service retirement allowance provided in this subsection for his or her membership
33 service earned after January 1, 2026."
34 SECTION 2.
35 This Act shall become effective on July 1, 2026, only if it is determined to have been
36 concurrently funded as provided in Chapter 20 of Title 47 of the Official Code of Georgia
37 Annotated, the "Public Retirement Systems Standards Law"; otherwise, this Act shall not
38 become effective and shall be automatically repealed in its entirety on July 1, 2026, as
39 required by subsection (a) of Code Section 47-20-50.
40 SECTION 3.
41 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
